{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:02:40,471", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_validation_result", "line": 185, "message": "{\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T16:02:40.471570\", \"task_id\": \"unknown\", \"task_objective\": \"Develop email template generator for interview invitations and follow-up communications\", \"result\": \"```python\\ndef generate_interview_invitation_email(candidate_name, job_title, interview_date, interview_time, interview_location, interviewer_name, interviewer_title, contact_email, additional_instructions=None):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Generates an email invitation for an interview.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        candidate_name (str): The name of the candidate.\\n        job_title (str): The title of the job the candidate is interviewing for.\\n        interview_date (str): The date of the interview (e.g., \\\"October 26, 202...\", \"validation_type\": \"text\", \"status\": \"completed\", \"feedback\": \"here are some feedbacks:\\n1. The templates currently hardcode “[Company Name]”, “[Your Name]”, and “[Your Title]” in the body/subject, requiring manual search-and-replace. Instead, pass these as parameters so the generator produces a fully customized email.\\n2. Return both subject and body separately (e.g., as a tuple or dict) to give callers flexibility in how they send the email.\\n3. Improve type hints and formatting consistency.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\nfrom typing import Optional, Tuple, Dict\\n\\ndef generate_interview_invitation_email(\\n    candidate_name: str,\\n    job_title: str,\\n    interview_date: str,\\n    interview_time: str,\\n    interview_location: str,\\n    interviewer_name: str,\\n    interviewer_title: str,\\n    company_name: str,\\n    sender_name: str,\\n    sender_title: str,\\n    contact_email: str,\\n    additional_instructions: Optional[str] = None\\n) -> Dict[str, str]:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Generates an email invitation for an interview.\\n\\n    Returns a dict with 'subject' and 'body' keys.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    subject = f\\\"Interview Invitation: {job_title} at {company_name}\\\"\\n\\n    body_lines = [\\n        f\\\"Dear {candidate_name},\\\",\\n        \\\"\\\",\\n        f\\\"Thank you for your interest in the {job_title} position at {company_name}.\\\",\\n        \\\"\\\",\\n        \\\"We are pleased to invite you to an interview to further discuss your qualifications.\\\",\\n        \\\"\\\",\\n        \\\"Here are the details of your interview:\\\",\\n        f\\\"- Date: {interview_date}\\\",\\n        f\\\"- Time: {interview_time}\\\",\\n        f\\\"- Location: {interview_location}\\\",\\n        \\\"\\\",\\n        f\\\"You will be interviewing with {interviewer_name}, {interviewer_title}.\\\",\\n        \\\"\\\"\\n    ]\\n\\n    if additional_instructions:\\n        body_lines.extend([\\n            f\\\"Additional Instructions: {additional_instructions}\\\",\\n            \\\"\\\"\\n        ])\\n\\n    body_lines.extend([\\n        f\\\"If you have any questions or need to reschedule, please contact us at {contact_email}.\\\",\\n        \\\"\\\",\\n        \\\"We look forward to meeting you!\\\",\\n        \\\"\\\",\\n        \\\"Sincerely,\\\",\\n        sender_name,\\n        sender_title,\\n        company_name\\n    ])\\n\\n    body = \\\"\\\\n\\\".join(body_lines)\\n    return {\\\"subject\\\": subject, \\\"body\\\": body}\\n\\n\\ndef generate_interview_followup_email(\\n    candidate_name: str,\\n    job_title: str,\\n    interviewer_name: str,\\n    company_name: str,\\n    sender_name: str,\\n    sender_title: str,\\n    contact_email: str,\\n    feedback_deadline: Optional[str] = None\\n) -> Dict[str, str]:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Generates a follow-up email to a candidate after an interview.\\n\\n    Returns a dict with 'subject' and 'body' keys.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    subject = f\\\"Follow-Up: {job_title} Interview at {company_name}\\\"\\n\\n    body_lines = [\\n        f\\\"Dear {candidate_name},\\\",\\n        \\\"\\\",\\n        f\\\"Thank you for taking the time to interview with {interviewer_name} for the {job_title} position at {company_name}.\\\",\\n        \\\"\\\",\\n        \\\"We are currently reviewing all applications and will be in touch with an update on the status of your application.\\\"\\n    ]\\n\\n    if feedback_deadline:\\n        body_lines.extend([\\n            \\\"\\\",\\n            f\\\"You can expect to hear from us by {feedback_deadline}.\\\",\\n        ])\\n\\n    body_lines.extend([\\n        \\\"\\\",\\n        f\\\"In the meantime, if you have any questions, please contact us at {contact_email}.\\\",\\n        \\\"\\\",\\n        \\\"Thank you again for your interest in our company.\\\",\\n        \\\"\\\",\\n        \\\"Sincerely,\\\",\\n        sender_name,\\n        sender_title,\\n        company_name\\n    ])\\n\\n    body = \\\"\\\\n\\\".join(body_lines)\\n    return {\\\"subject\\\": subject, \\\"body\\\": body}\\n\\n\\n# Example usage\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    invite = generate_interview_invitation_email(\\n        candidate_name=\\\"Jane Doe\\\",\\n        job_title=\\\"Software Engineer\\\",\\n        interview_date=\\\"November 2, 2023\\\",\\n        interview_time=\\\"2:00 PM - 3:00 PM\\\",\\n        interview_location=\\\"Zoom Meeting - Link: https://zoom.us/meeting/123\\\",\\n        interviewer_name=\\\"John Smith\\\",\\n        interviewer_title=\\\"Engineering Manager\\\",\\n        company_name=\\\"Acme Corp\\\",\\n        sender_name=\\\"Alice Johnson\\\",\\n        sender_title=\\\"Talent Acquisition Lead\\\",\\n        contact_email=\\\"recruiting@acme.com\\\",\\n        additional_instructions=\\\"Please have a copy of your portfolio handy.\\\"\\n    )\\n    print(\\\"Subject:\\\", invite[\\\"subject\\\"])\\n    print(invite[\\\"body\\\"])\\n\\n    followup = generate_interview_followup_email(\\n        candidate_name=\\\"Jane Doe\\\",\\n        job_title=\\\"Software Engineer\\\",\\n        interviewer_name=\\\"John Smith\\\",\\n        company_name=\\\"Acme Corp\\\",\\n        sender_name=\\\"Alice Johnson\\\",\\n        sender_title=\\\"Talent Acquisition Lead\\\",\\n        contact_email=\\\"recruiting@acme.com\\\",\\n        feedback_deadline=\\\"November 9, 2023\\\"\\n    )\\n    print(\\\"\\\\nSubject:\\\", followup[\\\"subject\\\"])\\n    print(followup[\\\"body\\\"])\\n```\"}"}
