{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:03:52,359", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_validation_result", "line": 185, "message": "{\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T16:03:52.359552\", \"task_id\": \"unknown\", \"task_objective\": \"Implement AI-based dynamic interview engine that generates technical and behavioral questions and follow-ups\", \"result\": \"```python\\nimport json\\nimport random\\n\\nclass InterviewEngine:\\n    def __init__(self, job_description_json, candidate_profile_json):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Initializes the InterviewEngine with job description and candidate profile.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            job_description_json (dict): Parsed job description in JSON format.\\n            candidate_profile_json (dict): Parsed candidate resume in JSON format.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.job_description = job_description_json\\n        self.candidate_profile =...\", \"validation_type\": \"text\", \"status\": \"completed\", \"feedback\": \"here are some feedbacks:\\n1. The current implementation uses static JSON files for questions and does not leverage the job description or candidate profile to tailor questions dynamically.\\n2. Follow-up questions are randomly selected rather than generated based on the candidate’s actual answer.\\n3. There is no AI integration—questions aren’t generated via an LLM, and the code doesn’t analyze the job description or resume.\\n4. The code doesn’t separate technical vs. behavioral prompts for the AI or adjust follow-ups based on context.\\n\\nTo meet the requirement of an “AI-based dynamic interview engine,” we should call an LLM (e.g. OpenAI API) to:\\n- Generate initial technical/behavioral questions based on the job description and candidate profile.\\n- Generate follow-up questions based on the candidate’s answer.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\nimport os\\nimport openai\\nimport json\\nimport time\\n\\nclass AIInterviewEngine:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    An AI-powered interview engine that dynamically generates\\n    technical and behavioral questions and follow-ups using OpenAI.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    def __init__(self, job_description: dict, candidate_profile: dict, model: str = \\\"gpt-3.5-turbo\\\"):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Args:\\n            job_description (dict): Parsed job description.\\n            candidate_profile (dict): Parsed candidate resume/profile.\\n            model (str): OpenAI model to use.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        openai.api_key = os.getenv(\\\"OPENAI_API_KEY\\\")\\n        if not openai.api_key:\\n            raise ValueError(\\\"Please set the OPENAI_API_KEY environment variable.\\\")\\n        self.job_description = job_description\\n        self.candidate_profile = candidate_profile\\n        self.model = model\\n\\n    def _call_llm(self, messages, temperature=0.7, max_tokens=200):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Helper to call ChatCompletion endpoint.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        for attempt in range(3):\\n            try:\\n                response = openai.ChatCompletion.create(\\n                    model=self.model,\\n                    messages=messages,\\n                    temperature=temperature,\\n                    max_tokens=max_tokens\\n                )\\n                return response.choices[0].message[\\\"content\\\"].strip()\\n            except openai.error.OpenAIError as e:\\n                print(f\\\"OpenAI API error: {e}. Retrying ({attempt+1}/3)...\\\")\\n                time.sleep(1)\\n        raise RuntimeError(\\\"Failed to get response from OpenAI after 3 attempts.\\\")\\n\\n    def generate_initial_question(self, qtype: str = \\\"technical\\\") -> str:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generate an initial question via LLM.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            qtype (str): \\\"technical\\\" or \\\"behavioral\\\".\\n        Returns:\\n            str: The generated question.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if qtype not in (\\\"technical\\\", \\\"behavioral\\\"):\\n            raise ValueError(\\\"qtype must be 'technical' or 'behavioral'.\\\")\\n\\n        prompt = (\\n            f\\\"You are a hiring interviewer. Given the job description:\\\\n\\\"\\n            f\\\"{json.dumps(self.job_description, indent=2)}\\\\n\\\\n\\\"\\n            f\\\"And the candidate profile:\\\\n\\\"\\n            f\\\"{json.dumps(self.candidate_profile, indent=2)}\\\\n\\\\n\\\"\\n            f\\\"Generate one {qtype} interview question tailored to this candidate \\\"\\n            f\\\"and role. Keep it clear and concise.\\\"\\n        )\\n        messages = [\\n            {\\\"role\\\": \\\"system\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"You are a helpful interviewer assistant.\\\"},\\n            {\\\"role\\\": \\\"user\\\", \\\"content\\\": prompt}\\n        ]\\n        return self._call_llm(messages)\\n\\n    def generate_follow_up(self, previous_question: str, candidate_answer: str) -> str:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generate a follow-up question based on the candidate's answer.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            previous_question (str): The last question asked.\\n            candidate_answer (str): The candidate's answer.\\n        Returns:\\n            str: The follow-up question.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        prompt = (\\n            f\\\"You asked: \\\\\\\"{previous_question}\\\\\\\".\\\\n\\\\n\\\"\\n            f\\\"The candidate answered: \\\\\\\"{candidate_answer}\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\n\\\"\\n            \\\"Generate a thoughtful follow-up question that digs deeper into their response.\\\"\\n        )\\n        messages = [\\n            {\\\"role\\\": \\\"system\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"You are an insightful interviewer assistant.\\\"},\\n            {\\\"role\\\": \\\"user\\\", \\\"content\\\": prompt}\\n        ]\\n        return self._call_llm(messages)\\n\\n    def conduct_interview(self, num_tech: int = 3, num_behav: int = 2):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Conducts the interview, printing questions and collecting answers via input().\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            list: Transcript of Q&A with follow-ups.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        transcript = []\\n\\n        def ask_and_record(qtype):\\n            # Generate initial\\n            q = self.generate_initial_question(qtype)\\n            print(f\\\"\\\\n{qtype.title()} Question: {q}\\\")\\n            ans = input(\\\"Your Answer: \\\")\\n            entry = {\\\"type\\\": qtype, \\\"question\\\": q, \\\"answer\\\": ans, \\\"follow_ups\\\": []}\\n\\n            # Generate follow-up\\n            fq = self.generate_follow_up(q, ans)\\n            print(f\\\"Follow-up: {fq}\\\")\\n            fans = input(\\\"Your Answer: \\\")\\n            entry[\\\"follow_ups\\\"].append({\\\"question\\\": fq, \\\"answer\\\": fans})\\n            return entry\\n\\n        # Technical\\n        for _ in range(num_tech):\\n            transcript.append(ask_and_record(\\\"technical\\\"))\\n\\n        # Behavioral\\n        for _ in range(num_behav):\\n            transcript.append(ask_and_record(\\\"behavioral\\\"))\\n\\n        return transcript\\n\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    # Example usage:\\n    job_description = {\\n        \\\"job_title\\\": \\\"Software Engineer\\\",\\n        \\\"responsibilities\\\": [\\n            \\\"Design and implement scalable web services\\\",\\n            \\\"Collaborate with data science team\\\"\\n        ],\\n        \\\"skills_required\\\": [\\\"Python\\\", \\\"REST APIs\\\", \\\"Docker\\\"]\\n    }\\n    candidate_profile = {\\n        \\\"name\\\": \\\"Alice Smith\\\",\\n        \\\"experience_years\\\": 4,\\n        \\\"skills\\\": [\\\"Python\\\", \\\"Flask\\\", \\\"Docker\\\", \\\"Kubernetes\\\"],\\n        \\\"projects\\\": [\\n            {\\\"name\\\": \\\"Inventory Microservice\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Built in Flask with PostgreSQL\\\"}\\n        ]\\n    }\\n\\n    engine = AIInterviewEngine(job_description, candidate_profile)\\n    transcript = engine.conduct_interview(num_tech=2, num_behav=1)\\n    print(\\\"\\\\nInterview Transcript:\\\")\\n    print(json.dumps(transcript, indent=2))\\n```\"}"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:04:09,417", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_2\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nPerform interview and candidate evaluation  for a candidate.\\n\\nyou should:\\n- Analyze job descriptions and candidate resumes\\n- Conduct dynamic AI-based interviews with technical and behavioral questions\\n- Generate follow-up questions based on candidate responses\\n- Evaluate candidate answers for relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy\\n- Score candidates across multiple evaluation categories\\n- Generate recruiter communication emails such as interview invitations and follow-ups\\n- Produce a final candidate evaluation report containing:\\n    - Resume-job match analysis\\n    - Interview summary\\n    - Technical assessment\\n    - Behavioral assessment\\n    - Strengths and weaknesses\\n    - Final recommendation and scoring breakdown\\n\\nFinal output: Evaluation report of candidate in .txt\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nTask task3:\\n  Objective: Implement AI-based dynamic interview engine that generates technical and behavioral questions and follow-ups\\n  Result: ```python\\nimport json\\nimport random\\n\\nclass InterviewEngine:\\n    def __init__(self, job_description_json, candidate_profile_json):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Initializes the InterviewEngine with job description and candidate profile.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            job_description_json (dict): Parsed job description in JSON format.\\n            candidate_profile_json (dict): Parsed candidate resume in JSON format.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.job_description = job_description_json\\n        self.candidate_profile = candidate_profile_json\\n        self.technical_questions = self.load_questions(\\\"technical\\\")\\n        self.behavioral_questions = self.load_questions(\\\"behavioral\\\")\\n        self.follow_up_questions = self.load_questions(\\\"follow_up\\\") # Load follow-up questions\\n\\n    def load_questions(self, question_type=\\\"technical\\\"):\\n          \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n          Loads questions from JSON files based on question type.\\n\\n          Args:\\n              question_type (str): Type of questions to load (\\\"technical\\\", \\\"behavioral\\\", \\\"follow_up\\\").\\n\\n          Returns:\\n              list: A list of dictionaries, each representing a question.\\n          \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n          try:\\n              with open(f\\\"questions_{question_type}.json\\\", \\\"r\\\") as f:\\n                  questions = json.load(f)\\n              return questions\\n          except FileNotFoundError:\\n              print(f\\\"Error: questions_{question_type}.json not found.  Returning empty list.\\\")\\n              return []\\n\\n    def generate_initial_question(self, question_type=\\\"technical\\\"):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates an initial technical or behavioral question.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            question_type (str): \\\"technical\\\" or \\\"behavioral\\\".\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            dict: A question dictionary.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if question_type == \\\"technical\\\":\\n            questions = self.technical_questions\\n        elif question_type == \\\"behavioral\\\":\\n            questions = self.behavioral_questions\\n        else:\\n            raise ValueError(\\\"Invalid question type.  Must be 'technical' or 'behavioral'.\\\")\\n\\n        if not questions:\\n            return {\\\"question\\\": \\\"No questions available for this type.\\\"}\\n\\n        return random.choice(questions)\\n\\n    def generate_follow_up_question(self, candidate_answer):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates a follow-up question based on the candidate's answer.  This is a simplified\\n        implementation that randomly selects a follow-up question.  A more sophisticated\\n        implementation would analyze the candidate's answer and select a follow-up question\\n        that is relevant to the answer.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            candidate_answer (str): The candidate's answer to the previous question.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            dict: A follow-up question dictionary.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if not self.follow_up_questions:\\n            return {\\\"question\\\": \\\"No follow-up questions available.\\\"}\\n\\n        return random.choice(self.follow_up_questions)\\n\\n    def conduct_interview(self, num_technical_questions=3, num_behavioral_questions=2):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Conducts a dynamic interview with technical and behavioral questions.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            num_technical_questions (int): Number of technical questions to ask.\\n            num_behavioral_questions (int): Number of behavioral questions to ask.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            list: A list of dictionaries, each containing a question, the candidate's answer, and any follow-up questions/answers.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        interview_transcript = []\\n\\n        # Technical Questions\\n        for _ in range(num_technical_questions):\\n            question_data = self.generate_initial_question(question_type=\\\"technical\\\")\\n            question = question_data[\\\"question\\\"]\\n            print(f\\\"Technical Question: {question}\\\")\\n            candidate_answer = input(\\\"Your Answer: \\\")  # Simulate candidate answering\\n            interview_transcript.append({\\\"question\\\": question, \\\"answer\\\": candidate_answer, \\\"follow_ups\\\": []})\\n\\n            # Generate and ask a follow-up question\\n            follow_up_data = self.generate_follow_up_question(candidate_answer)\\n            follow_up_question = follow_up_data[\\\"question\\\"]\\n            print(f\\\"Follow-up: {follow_up_question}\\\")\\n            follow_up_answer = input(\\\"Your Answer: \\\") # Simulate candidate answering\\n            interview_transcript[-1][\\\"follow_ups\\\"].append({\\\"question\\\": follow_up_question, \\\"answer\\\": follow_up_answer})\\n\\n\\n        # Behavioral Questions\\n        for _ in range(num_behavioral_questions):\\n            question_data = self.generate_initial_question(question_type=\\\"behavioral\\\")\\n            question = question_data[\\\"question\\\"]\\n            print(f\\\"Behavioral Question: {question}\\\")\\n            candidate_answer = input(\\\"Your Answer: \\\")  # Simulate candidate answering\\n            interview_transcript.append({\\\"question\\\": question, \\\"answer\\\": candidate_answer, \\\"follow_ups\\\": []})\\n\\n            # Generate and ask a follow-up question\\n            follow_up_data = self.generate_follow_up_question(candidate_answer)\\n            follow_up_question = follow_up_data[\\\"question\\\"]\\n            print(f\\\"Follow-up: {follow_up_question}\\\")\\n            follow_up_answer = input(\\\"Your Answer: \\\") # Simulate candidate answering\\n            interview_transcript[-1][\\\"follow_ups\\\"].append({\\\"question\\\": follow_up_question, \\\"answer\\\": follow_up_answer})\\n\\n\\n        return interview_transcript\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Sample Usage (replace with actual JSON data)\\n    job_description_data = {\\n      \\\"job_title\\\": \\\"Software Engineer\\\",\\n      \\\"skills\\\": {\\n        \\\"technical\\\": [\\\"Python\\\", \\\"Data Analysis\\\"]\\n      }\\n    }\\n    candidate_profile_data = {\\n      \\\"candidate_profile\\\": {\\n        \\\"skills\\\": [\\\"Python\\\", \\\"Machine Learning\\\"]\\n      }\\n    }\\n\\n    # Create dummy question files\\n    with open(\\\"questions_technical.json\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n        json.dump([{\\\"question\\\": \\\"Explain the difference between lists and tuples in Python.\\\"}, {\\\"question\\\": \\\"What is the time complexity of a dictionary lookup?\\\"}], f)\\n    with open(\\\"questions_behavioral.json\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n        json.dump([{\\\"question\\\": \\\"Tell me about a time you failed.\\\"}, {\\\"question\\\": \\\"Describe a time you had to work with a difficult team member.\\\"}], f)\\n    with open(\\\"questions_follow_up.json\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n        json.dump([{\\\"question\\\": \\\"Can you elaborate on that?\\\"}, {\\\"question\\\": \\\"What were the key takeaways?\\\"}], f)\\n\\n\\n\\n    engine = InterviewEngine(job_description_data, candidate_profile_data)\\n    interview_transcript = engine.conduct_interview()\\n\\n    print(\\\"\\\\nInterview Transcript:\\\")\\n    print(json.dumps(interview_transcript, indent=4))\\n```\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task5:\\n  Objective: Create scoring aggregation module to compute final scores across match, technical, and behavioral categories\\nTask task7:\\n  Objective: Generate final candidate evaluation report (.txt) including match analysis, interview summary, assessments, strengths/weaknesses, and recommendation\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nBuild answer evaluation module to assess relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy of responses\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPython code\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\nimport json\\n\\nclass AnswerEvaluator:\\n    def __init__(self, job_description_json, candidate_profile_json):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Initializes the AnswerEvaluator with job description and candidate profile.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            job_description_json (dict): Parsed job description in JSON format.\\n            candidate_profile_json (dict): Parsed candidate resume in JSON format.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.job_description = job_description_json\\n        self.candidate_profile = candidate_profile_json\\n\\n    def evaluate_answer(self, question, answer, question_type=\\\"technical\\\"):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Evaluates a candidate's answer based on relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            question (str): The question asked.\\n            answer (str): The candidate's answer.\\n            question_type (str): \\\"technical\\\" or \\\"behavioral\\\".\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            dict: A dictionary containing evaluation scores and feedback.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        evaluation = {\\n            \\\"relevance\\\": self.evaluate_relevance(question, answer),\\n            \\\"depth\\\": self.evaluate_depth(answer),\\n            \\\"confidence\\\": self.evaluate_confidence(answer),\\n        }\\n\\n        if question_type == \\\"technical\\\":\\n            evaluation[\\\"technical_accuracy\\\"] = self.evaluate_technical_accuracy(question, answer)\\n        else:\\n            evaluation[\\\"technical_accuracy\\\"] = None\\n\\n        evaluation[\\\"overall_score\\\"] = self.calculate_overall_score(evaluation)\\n        evaluation[\\\"feedback\\\"] = self.generate_feedback(evaluation, question_type)\\n\\n        return evaluation\\n\\n    def evaluate_relevance(self, question, answer):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Evaluates the relevance of the answer to the question.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            question (str): The question asked.\\n            answer (str): The candidate's answer.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            int: Relevance score (0-5).\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # Placeholder implementation - needs to be improved with NLP techniques\\n        if not answer:\\n            return 0  # No answer provided\\n        keywords_in_question = question.lower().split()\\n        keywords_in_answer = answer.lower().split()\\n        common_keywords = set(keywords_in_question) & set(keywords_in_answer)\\n        score = min(5, len(common_keywords)) # Cap the score at 5\\n        return score\\n\\n    def evaluate_depth(self, answer):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Evaluates the depth of the answer.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            answer (str): The candidate's answer.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            int: Depth score (0-5).\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # Placeholder implementation - needs to be improved with NLP techniques\\n        length = len(answer.split())\\n        if length < 10:\\n            return 1\\n        elif length < 50:\\n            return 3\\n        else:\\n            return 5\\n\\n    def evaluate_confidence(self, answer):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Evaluates the confidence conveyed in the answer.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            answer (str): The candidate's answer.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            int: Confidence score (0-5).\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # Placeholder implementation - analyze tone, certainty words, etc.\\n        # Example: Check for hesitant language (\\\"I think\\\", \\\"maybe\\\", \\\"I'm not sure\\\")\\n        hesitation_words = [\\\"I think\\\", \\\"maybe\\\", \\\"I'm not sure\\\", \\\"I believe\\\"]\\n        hesitation_count = sum([answer.lower().count(word) for word in hesitation_words])\\n\\n        if hesitation_count > 2:\\n          return 2\\n        elif hesitation_count > 0:\\n            return 3\\n        else:\\n            return 5\\n\\n    def evaluate_technical_accuracy(self, question, answer):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Evaluates the technical accuracy of the answer.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            question (str): The technical question asked.\\n            answer (str): The candidate's answer.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            int: Technical accuracy score (0-5).\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # Placeholder implementation - requires domain-specific knowledge\\n        # This is a very basic example.  In a real application, this would\\n        # involve more sophisticated techniques such as:\\n        #   - Knowledge graphs\\n        #   - Code execution and testing\\n        #   - Comparison to expected answers\\n        keywords_in_question = question.lower().split()\\n        keywords_in_answer = answer.lower().split()\\n\\n        # Check for specific keywords related to common technical concepts\\n        if \\\"time complexity\\\" in question.lower() and (\\\"O(n)\\\" in answer or \\\"O(1)\\\" in answer):\\n            return 5\\n        elif \\\"linked list\\\" in question.lower() and \\\"nodes\\\" in answer.lower() and \\\"pointers\\\" in answer.lower():\\n            return 4\\n        else:\\n            return 3 # Default score if no specific keywords are found\\n\\n    def calculate_overall_score(self, evaluation):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Calculates the overall score based on individual evaluation metrics.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            evaluation (dict): A dictionary containing evaluation scores.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            float: Overall score (0-5).\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        total_score = evaluation[\\\"relevance\\\"] + evaluation[\\\"depth\\\"] + evaluation[\\\"confidence\\\"]\\n        if evaluation[\\\"technical_accuracy\\\"] is not None:\\n            total_score += evaluation[\\\"technical_accuracy\\\"]\\n            num_metrics = 4\\n        else:\\n            num_metrics = 3\\n\\n        return total_score / num_metrics\\n\\n    def generate_feedback(self, evaluation, question_type):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates feedback based on the evaluation scores.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            evaluation (dict): A dictionary containing evaluation scores.\\n            question_type (str): \\\"technical\\\" or \\\"behavioral\\\".\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            str: Feedback string.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        feedback = \\\"\\\"\\n        if evaluation[\\\"relevance\\\"] < 3:\\n            feedback += \\\"The answer could be more relevant to the question. \\\"\\n        if evaluation[\\\"depth\\\"] < 3:\\n            feedback += \\\"The answer could be more in-depth. \\\"\\n        if evaluation[\\\"confidence\\\"] < 3:\\n            feedback += \\\"The answer could be delivered with more confidence. \\\"\\n        if question_type == \\\"technical\\\" and evaluation[\\\"technical_accuracy\\\"] < 3:\\n            feedback += \\\"The technical accuracy of the answer could be improved. \\\"\\n\\n        if not feedback:\\n            feedback = \\\"The answer was well-received.\\\"\\n\\n        return feedback\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Sample Usage\\n    job_description_data = {\\n        \\\"job_title\\\": \\\"Software Engineer\\\",\\n        \\\"skills\\\": {\\n            \\\"technical\\\": [\\\"Python\\\", \\\"Data Analysis\\\"]\\n        }\\n    }\\n    candidate_profile_data = {\\n        \\\"candidate_profile\\\": {\\n            \\\"skills\\\": [\\\"Python\\\", \\\"Machine Learning\\\"]\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    evaluator = AnswerEvaluator(job_description_data, candidate_profile_data)\\n\\n    technical_question = \\\"Explain the difference between lists and tuples in Python.\\\"\\n    technical_answer = \\\"Lists are mutable, while tuples are immutable.\\\"\\n    technical_evaluation = evaluator.evaluate_answer(technical_question, technical_answer, \\\"technical\\\")\\n    print(\\\"Technical Question Evaluation:\\\", technical_evaluation)\\n\\n    behavioral_question = \\\"Tell me about a time you failed.\\\"\\n    behavioral_answer = \\\"I once missed a deadline because I underestimated the workload.\\\"\\n    behavioral_evaluation = evaluator.evaluate_answer(behavioral_question, behavioral_answer, \\\"behavioral\\\")\\n    print(\\\"Behavioral Question Evaluation:\\\", behavioral_evaluation)\\n```\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T16:04:09.417810\"\n}"}
