{"timestamp": "2026-05-26 16:04:47,756", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_3\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nPerform interview and candidate evaluation  for a candidate.\\n\\nyou should:\\n- Analyze job descriptions and candidate resumes\\n- Conduct dynamic AI-based interviews with technical and behavioral questions\\n- Generate follow-up questions based on candidate responses\\n- Evaluate candidate answers for relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy\\n- Score candidates across multiple evaluation categories\\n- Generate recruiter communication emails such as interview invitations and follow-ups\\n- Produce a final candidate evaluation report containing:\\n    - Resume-job match analysis\\n    - Interview summary\\n    - Technical assessment\\n    - Behavioral assessment\\n    - Strengths and weaknesses\\n    - Final recommendation and scoring breakdown\\n\\nFinal output: Evaluation report of candidate in .txt\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nTask task2:\\n  Objective: Develop resume–job match analysis algorithm to produce match scores and key alignment points\\n  Result: ```json\\n{\\n  \\\"resume_job_match_analysis_algorithm\\\": {\\n    \\\"version\\\": \\\"1.0\\\",\\n    \\\"description\\\": \\\"Algorithm to match a candidate's resume against a job description, providing a match score and identifying key alignment points.\\\",\\n    \\\"component_weights\\\": {\\n      \\\"experience\\\": 0.4,\\n      \\\"skills\\\": 0.3,\\n      \\\"education\\\": 0.15,\\n      \\\"certifications\\\": 0.1,\\n      \\\"projects\\\": 0.05\\n    },\\n    \\\"keyword_extraction\\\": {\\n      \\\"method\\\": \\\"SpaCy NLP + Custom Dictionary\\\",\\n      \\\"steps\\\": [\\n        \\\"1. Input text: Job description and resume sections.\\\",\\n        \\\"2. Preprocessing: Lowercasing, punctuation removal, stop word removal using SpaCy.\\\",\\n        \\\"3. Lemmatization: Reduce words to their base form using SpaCy.\\\",\\n        \\\"4. Named Entity Recognition (NER): Identify key entities (e.g., skills, companies, job titles) using SpaCy's NER.\\\",\\n        \\\"5. Custom Dictionary Augmentation: Enrich extracted keywords with synonyms and related terms from a domain-specific dictionary (e.g., technical skills, HR terms).\\\",\\n        \\\"6. TF-IDF Scoring: Calculate TF-IDF scores for each term in both the job description and resume sections.\\\",\\n        \\\"7. Keyword Selection: Select top N keywords based on TF-IDF scores and relevance (e.g., filtering out overly generic terms).\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    \\\"similarity_calculation\\\": {\\n      \\\"experience\\\": {\\n        \\\"method\\\": \\\"Cosine Similarity on Keyword Vectors\\\",\\n        \\\"description\\\": \\\"Calculate the cosine similarity between keyword vectors extracted from the 'experience' sections of the job description and resume.  Each experience entry is treated as a document.\\\",\\n        \\\"details\\\": \\\"Keywords are weighted by TF-IDF.  A minimum overlap threshold (e.g., 0.1) can be applied to avoid matching unrelated experiences.\\\",\\n        \\\"weight\\\": 1.0\\n      },\\n      \\\"skills\\\": {\\n        \\\"method\\\": \\\"Jaccard Similarity with Synonym Expansion\\\",\\n        \\\"description\\\": \\\"Calculate the Jaccard similarity (intersection over union) between skill sets listed in the job description and resume. Synonym expansion is performed using WordNet or a custom thesaurus.\\\",\\n        \\\"details\\\": \\\"Skills are normalized (e.g., 'Java' and 'Java Programming' are considered the same).  Skills are stemmed before comparison.\\\",\\n        \\\"weight\\\": 1.0\\n      },\\n      \\\"education\\\": {\\n        \\\"method\\\": \\\"String Similarity and Semantic Matching\\\",\\n        \\\"description\\\": \\\"Match education entries based on degree name, major, and institution. A combination of string similarity (Levenshtein distance) and semantic matching (using word embeddings) is used.\\\",\\n        \\\"details\\\": \\\"Higher weight is given to exact matches of degree names. Semantic matching is used to identify related majors (e.g., 'Computer Science' and 'Software Engineering').\\\",\\n        \\\"weight\\\": 0.8\\n      },\\n      \\\"certifications\\\": {\\n        \\\"method\\\": \\\"Exact and Fuzzy String Matching\\\",\\n        \\\"description\\\": \\\"Identify matching certifications using both exact and fuzzy string matching (e.g., using the FuzzyWuzzy library).\\\",\\n        \\\"details\\\": \\\"Partial matches (e.g., a slightly different certification name) receive a lower score.  Certifications from reputable organizations receive a higher weight.\\\",\\n        \\\"weight\\\": 0.9\\n      },\\n      \\\"projects\\\": {\\n        \\\"method\\\": \\\"Keyword Overlap and Description Similarity\\\",\\n        \\\"description\\\": \\\"Analyzes project descriptions in the resume for keyword overlap with the job description's required skills and responsibilities.  Cosine similarity is used to compare project descriptions.\\\",\\n        \\\"details\\\": \\\"Projects demonstrating relevant experience (e.g., AI projects for an AI role) are weighted higher.\\\",\\n         \\\"weight\\\": 0.7\\n      }\\n    },\\n    \\\"scoring\\\": {\\n      \\\"detailed\\\": {\\n        \\\"experience\\\": \\\"score_experience = similarity_experience * component_weights['experience']\\\",\\n        \\\"skills\\\": \\\"score_skills = similarity_skills * component_weights['skills']\\\",\\n        \\\"education\\\": \\\"score_education = similarity_education * component_weights['education']\\\",\\n        \\\"certifications\\\": \\\"score_certifications = similarity_certifications * component_weights['certifications']\\\",\\n        \\\"projects\\\": \\\"score_projects = similarity_projects * component_weights['projects']\\\"\\n      },\\n      \\\"aggregate\\\": {\\n        \\\"formula\\\": \\\"match_score = score_experience + score_skills + score_education + score_certifications + score_projects\\\",\\n        \\\"normalization\\\": \\\"match_score = min(1.0, match_score)  # Ensure match_score is between 0.0 and 1.0\\\"\\n      }\\n    },\\n    \\\"match_thresholds\\\": {\\n      \\\"excellent\\\": 0.85,\\n      \\\"good\\\": 0.7,\\n      \\\"average\\\": 0.5,\\n      \\\"poor\\\": 0.3\\n    },\\n    \\\"output_structure\\\": {\\n      \\\"match_score\\\": \\\"Float between 0.0 and 1.0 indicating overall match strength.\\\",\\n      \\\"key_alignment_points\\\": {\\n        \\\"experience\\\": [\\\"List of top matched experience keywords and corresponding job responsibilities.\\\"],\\n        \\\"skills\\\": [\\\"List of matched skill keywords and indication of proficiency level (if available).\\\"],\\n        \\\"education\\\": [\\\"Matched degree names, majors, and institutions. Indication of relevance to the job.\\\"],\\n        \\\"certifications\\\": [\\\"Matched certification names and issuing organizations.\\\"],\\n        \\\"projects\\\": [\\\"List of projects that demonstrate key skills or experience related to the job description.\\\"]\\n      },\\n      \\\"detailed_analysis\\\": {\\n        \\\"experience_match\\\": {\\n          \\\"score\\\": \\\"Float representing the experience match score.\\\",\\n          \\\"matched_keywords\\\": [\\\"List of keywords matched in the experience section.\\\"],\\n          \\\"unmatched_keywords\\\": [\\\"List of keywords from the job description not found in the experience section.\\\"]\\n        },\\n        \\\"skills_match\\\": {\\n          \\\"score\\\": \\\"Float representing the skills match score.\\\",\\n          \\\"matched_keywords\\\": [\\\"List of skills matched.\\\"],\\n          \\\"unmatched_keywords\\\": [\\\"List of required skills not found.\\\"]\\n        },\\n        \\\"education_match\\\": {\\n          \\\"score\\\": \\\"Float representing the education match score.\\\",\\n          \\\"matched_keywords\\\": [\\\"List of matched education details.\\\"],\\n          \\\"unmatched_keywords\\\": [\\\"List of required education details not found.\\\"]\\n        },\\n        \\\"certifications_match\\\": {\\n          \\\"score\\\": \\\"Float representing the certifications match score.\\\",\\n          \\\"matched_keywords\\\": [\\\"List of matched certifications.\\\"],\\n          \\\"unmatched_keywords\\\": [\\\"List of required certifications not found.\\\"]\\n        },\\n         \\\"projects_match\\\": {\\n          \\\"score\\\": \\\"Float representing the projects match score.\\\",\\n          \\\"matched_keywords\\\": [\\\"List of keywords matched in the projects section.\\\"],\\n          \\\"unmatched_keywords\\\": [\\\"List of keywords from the job description not found in the projects section.\\\"]\\n        },\\n        \\\"overall_summary\\\": \\\"String summarizing the candidate's strengths and weaknesses based on the resume-job match. Highlights key areas of alignment and gaps.\\\"\\n      },\\n      \\\"recommendation\\\": \\\"String suggesting a course of action based on the match_score and detailed analysis (e.g., 'Highly recommended for interview', 'Consider for further evaluation', 'Not a strong match').\\\"\\n    },\\n    \\\"dependencies\\\": [\\n      \\\"SpaCy NLP library\\\",\\n      \\\"WordNet or a custom thesaurus for synonym expansion\\\",\\n      \\\"FuzzyWuzzy library for fuzzy string matching\\\"\\n    ]\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\nTask task4:\\n  Objective: Build answer evaluation module to assess relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy of responses\\n  Result: ```python\\nimport json\\n\\nclass AnswerEvaluator:\\n    def __init__(self, job_description_json, candidate_profile_json):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Initializes the AnswerEvaluator with job description and candidate profile.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            job_description_json (dict): Parsed job description in JSON format.\\n            candidate_profile_json (dict): Parsed candidate resume in JSON format.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.job_description = job_description_json\\n        self.candidate_profile = candidate_profile_json\\n\\n    def evaluate_answer(self, question, answer, question_type=\\\"technical\\\"):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Evaluates a candidate's answer based on relevance, depth, confidence, and technical accuracy.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            question (str): The question asked.\\n            answer (str): The candidate's answer.\\n            question_type (str): \\\"technical\\\" or \\\"behavioral\\\".\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            dict: A dictionary containing evaluation scores and feedback.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        evaluation = {\\n            \\\"relevance\\\": self.evaluate_relevance(question, answer),\\n            \\\"depth\\\": self.evaluate_depth(answer),\\n            \\\"confidence\\\": self.evaluate_confidence(answer),\\n        }\\n\\n        if question_type == \\\"technical\\\":\\n            evaluation[\\\"technical_accuracy\\\"] = self.evaluate_technical_accuracy(question, answer)\\n        else:\\n            evaluation[\\\"technical_accuracy\\\"] = None\\n\\n        evaluation[\\\"overall_score\\\"] = self.calculate_overall_score(evaluation)\\n        evaluation[\\\"feedback\\\"] = self.generate_feedback(evaluation, question_type)\\n\\n        return evaluation\\n\\n    def evaluate_relevance(self, question, answer):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Evaluates the relevance of the answer to the question.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            question (str): The question asked.\\n            answer (str): The candidate's answer.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            int: Relevance score (0-5).\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # Placeholder implementation - needs to be improved with NLP techniques\\n        if not answer:\\n            return 0  # No answer provided\\n        keywords_in_question = question.lower().split()\\n        keywords_in_answer = answer.lower().split()\\n        common_keywords = set(keywords_in_question) & set(keywords_in_answer)\\n        score = min(5, len(common_keywords)) # Cap the score at 5\\n        return score\\n\\n    def evaluate_depth(self, answer):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Evaluates the depth of the answer.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            answer (str): The candidate's answer.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            int: Depth score (0-5).\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # Placeholder implementation - needs to be improved with NLP techniques\\n        length = len(answer.split())\\n        if length < 10:\\n            return 1\\n        elif length < 50:\\n            return 3\\n        else:\\n            return 5\\n\\n    def evaluate_confidence(self, answer):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Evaluates the confidence conveyed in the answer.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            answer (str): The candidate's answer.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            int: Confidence score (0-5).\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # Placeholder implementation - analyze tone, certainty words, etc.\\n        # Example: Check for hesitant language (\\\"I think\\\", \\\"maybe\\\", \\\"I'm not sure\\\")\\n        hesitation_words = [\\\"I think\\\", \\\"maybe\\\", \\\"I'm not sure\\\", \\\"I believe\\\"]\\n        hesitation_count = sum([answer.lower().count(word) for word in hesitation_words])\\n\\n        if hesitation_count > 2:\\n          return 2\\n        elif hesitation_count > 0:\\n            return 3\\n        else:\\n            return 5\\n\\n    def evaluate_technical_accuracy(self, question, answer):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Evaluates the technical accuracy of the answer.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            question (str): The technical question asked.\\n            answer (str): The candidate's answer.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            int: Technical accuracy score (0-5).\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # Placeholder implementation - requires domain-specific knowledge\\n        # This is a very basic example.  In a real application, this would\\n        # involve more sophisticated techniques such as:\\n        #   - Knowledge graphs\\n        #   - Code execution and testing\\n        #   - Comparison to expected answers\\n        keywords_in_question = question.lower().split()\\n        keywords_in_answer = answer.lower().split()\\n\\n        # Check for specific keywords related to common technical concepts\\n        if \\\"time complexity\\\" in question.lower() and (\\\"O(n)\\\" in answer or \\\"O(1)\\\" in answer):\\n            return 5\\n        elif \\\"linked list\\\" in question.lower() and \\\"nodes\\\" in answer.lower() and \\\"pointers\\\" in answer.lower():\\n            return 4\\n        else:\\n            return 3 # Default score if no specific keywords are found\\n\\n    def calculate_overall_score(self, evaluation):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Calculates the overall score based on individual evaluation metrics.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            evaluation (dict): A dictionary containing evaluation scores.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            float: Overall score (0-5).\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        total_score = evaluation[\\\"relevance\\\"] + evaluation[\\\"depth\\\"] + evaluation[\\\"confidence\\\"]\\n        if evaluation[\\\"technical_accuracy\\\"] is not None:\\n            total_score += evaluation[\\\"technical_accuracy\\\"]\\n            num_metrics = 4\\n        else:\\n            num_metrics = 3\\n\\n        return total_score / num_metrics\\n\\n    def generate_feedback(self, evaluation, question_type):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates feedback based on the evaluation scores.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            evaluation (dict): A dictionary containing evaluation scores.\\n            question_type (str): \\\"technical\\\" or \\\"behavioral\\\".\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            str: Feedback string.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        feedback = \\\"\\\"\\n        if evaluation[\\\"relevance\\\"] < 3:\\n            feedback += \\\"The answer could be more relevant to the question. \\\"\\n        if evaluation[\\\"depth\\\"] < 3:\\n            feedback += \\\"The answer could be more in-depth. \\\"\\n        if evaluation[\\\"confidence\\\"] < 3:\\n            feedback += \\\"The answer could be delivered with more confidence. \\\"\\n        if question_type == \\\"technical\\\" and evaluation[\\\"technical_accuracy\\\"] < 3:\\n            feedback += \\\"The technical accuracy of the answer could be improved. \\\"\\n\\n        if not feedback:\\n            feedback = \\\"The answer was well-received.\\\"\\n\\n        return feedback\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Sample Usage\\n    job_description_data = {\\n        \\\"job_title\\\": \\\"Software Engineer\\\",\\n        \\\"skills\\\": {\\n            \\\"technical\\\": [\\\"Python\\\", \\\"Data Analysis\\\"]\\n        }\\n    }\\n    candidate_profile_data = {\\n        \\\"candidate_profile\\\": {\\n            \\\"skills\\\": [\\\"Python\\\", \\\"Machine Learning\\\"]\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    evaluator = AnswerEvaluator(job_description_data, candidate_profile_data)\\n\\n    technical_question = \\\"Explain the difference between lists and tuples in Python.\\\"\\n    technical_answer = \\\"Lists are mutable, while tuples are immutable.\\\"\\n    technical_evaluation = evaluator.evaluate_answer(technical_question, technical_answer, \\\"technical\\\")\\n    print(\\\"Technical Question Evaluation:\\\", technical_evaluation)\\n\\n    behavioral_question = \\\"Tell me about a time you failed.\\\"\\n    behavioral_answer = \\\"I once missed a deadline because I underestimated the workload.\\\"\\n    behavioral_evaluation = evaluator.evaluate_answer(behavioral_question, behavioral_answer, \\\"behavioral\\\")\\n    print(\\\"Behavioral Question Evaluation:\\\", behavioral_evaluation)\\n```\\nTask task5:\\n  Objective: Create scoring aggregation module to compute final scores across match, technical, and behavioral categories\\n  Result: ```python\\nclass ScoringAggregator:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Aggregates scores from resume matching, technical assessments, and behavioral assessments\\n    to produce a final candidate score and evaluation.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    def __init__(self, resume_job_match_weight=0.3, technical_assessment_weight=0.4, behavioral_assessment_weight=0.3):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Initializes the ScoringAggregator with weights for each assessment category.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            resume_job_match_weight (float): Weight for the resume-job match score (default: 0.3).\\n            technical_assessment_weight (float): Weight for the technical assessment score (default: 0.4).\\n            behavioral_assessment_weight (float): Weight for the behavioral assessment score (default: 0.3).\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if sum([resume_job_match_weight, technical_assessment_weight, behavioral_assessment_weight]) != 1.0:\\n            raise ValueError(\\\"The sum of the weights must equal 1.0\\\")\\n\\n        self.resume_job_match_weight = resume_job_match_weight\\n        self.technical_assessment_weight = technical_assessment_weight\\n        self.behavioral_assessment_weight = behavioral_assessment_weight\\n\\n    def aggregate_scores(self, resume_job_match_score, technical_assessment_scores, behavioral_assessment_scores):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Aggregates scores from different assessment categories into a final score.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            resume_job_match_score (float): The resume-job match score (0.0 to 1.0).\\n            technical_assessment_scores (list of floats): A list of technical assessment scores (0.0 to 5.0).\\n            behavioral_assessment_scores (list of floats): A list of behavioral assessment scores (0.0 to 5.0).\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            dict: A dictionary containing the aggregated score and individual component scores.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n        # Calculate the average technical assessment score\\n        if technical_assessment_scores:\\n            avg_technical_score = sum(technical_assessment_scores) / len(technical_assessment_scores)\\n        else:\\n            avg_technical_score = 0.0\\n\\n        # Calculate the average behavioral assessment score\\n        if behavioral_assessment_scores:\\n            avg_behavioral_score = sum(behavioral_assessment_scores) / len(behavioral_assessment_scores)\\n        else:\\n            avg_behavioral_score = 0.0\\n\\n        # Normalize the technical and behavioral scores to be between 0.0 and 1.0\\n        normalized_technical_score = avg_technical_score / 5.0 if avg_technical_score > 0 else 0.0\\n        normalized_behavioral_score = avg_behavioral_score / 5.0 if avg_behavioral_score > 0 else 0.0\\n\\n        # Calculate the weighted final score\\n        final_score = (\\n            self.resume_job_match_weight * resume_job_match_score +\\n            self.technical_assessment_weight * normalized_technical_score +\\n            self.behavioral_assessment_weight * normalized_behavioral_score\\n        )\\n\\n        return {\\n            \\\"final_score\\\": final_score,\\n            \\\"resume_job_match_score\\\": resume_job_match_score,\\n            \\\"avg_technical_score\\\": avg_technical_score,\\n            \\\"avg_behavioral_score\\\": avg_behavioral_score,\\n            \\\"weighted_resume_score\\\": self.resume_job_match_weight * resume_job_match_score,\\n            \\\"weighted_technical_score\\\": self.technical_assessment_weight * normalized_technical_score,\\n            \\\"weighted_behavioral_score\\\": self.behavioral_assessment_weight * normalized_behavioral_score,\\n        }\\n\\n    def generate_recommendation(self, final_score, thresholds=None):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Generates a recommendation based on the final score.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            final_score (float): The final aggregated score.\\n            thresholds (dict, optional): A dictionary containing thresholds for different recommendation levels.\\n                                          Defaults to {\\\"strong_yes\\\": 0.85, \\\"yes\\\": 0.7, \\\"maybe\\\": 0.5, \\\"no\\\": 0.3}.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            str: A recommendation string.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if thresholds is None:\\n            thresholds = {\\\"strong_yes\\\": 0.85, \\\"yes\\\": 0.7, \\\"maybe\\\": 0.5, \\\"no\\\": 0.3}\\n\\n        if final_score >= thresholds[\\\"strong_yes\\\"]:\\n            return \\\"Strongly Recommend for Hire\\\"\\n        elif final_score >= thresholds[\\\"yes\\\"]:\\n            return \\\"Recommend for Hire\\\"\\n        elif final_score >= thresholds[\\\"maybe\\\"]:\\n            return \\\"Consider for Further Evaluation\\\"\\n        else:\\n            return \\\"Not Recommended for Hire\\\"\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example Usage\\n    aggregator = ScoringAggregator(resume_job_match_weight=0.3, technical_assessment_weight=0.4, behavioral_assessment_weight=0.3)\\n\\n    # Sample scores\\n    resume_match_score = 0.8\\n    technical_scores = [4.0, 4.5, 3.5]\\n    behavioral_scores = [3.0, 4.0, 5.0]\\n\\n    # Aggregate the scores\\n    aggregated_results = aggregator.aggregate_scores(resume_match_score, technical_scores, behavioral_scores)\\n    print(\\\"Aggregated Results:\\\", aggregated_results)\\n\\n    # Generate a recommendation\\n    recommendation = aggregator.generate_recommendation(aggregated_results[\\\"final_score\\\"])\\n    print(\\\"Recommendation:\\\", recommendation)\\n```\\n\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nNo downstream objectives available.\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nGenerate final candidate evaluation report (.txt) including match analysis, interview summary, assessments, strengths/weaknesses, and recommendation\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPlain text\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```text\\nCandidate Evaluation Report\\n\\nCandidate: [Candidate Name - Replace with actual name]\\nDate: [Date of Evaluation - Replace with actual date]\\nPosition: [Job Title - Replace with actual job title]\\n\\nI. Resume-Job Match Analysis:\\n[Generated using task2 - resume_job_match_analysis_algorithm]\\n\\nMatch Score: [Value - Float between 0.0 and 1.0]\\nOverall Assessment: [Excellent/Good/Average/Poor based on match_thresholds]\\n\\nKey Alignment Points:\\n  - Experience: [List of top matched experience keywords and corresponding job responsibilities.]\\n  - Skills: [List of matched skill keywords and indication of proficiency level (if available).]\\n  - Education: [Matched degree names, majors, and institutions. Indication of relevance to the job.]\\n  - Certifications: [Matched certification names and issuing organizations.]\\n  - Projects: [List of projects that demonstrate key skills or experience related to the job description.]\\n\\nDetailed Analysis:\\n  - Experience Match:\\n    - Score: [Value - Float]\\n    - Matched Keywords: [List]\\n    - Unmatched Keywords: [List]\\n  - Skills Match:\\n    - Score: [Value - Float]\\n    - Matched Keywords: [List]\\n    - Unmatched Keywords: [List]\\n  - Education Match:\\n    - Score: [Value - Float]\\n    - Matched Keywords: [List]\\n    - Unmatched Keywords: [List]\\n  - Certifications Match:\\n    - Score: [Value - Float]\\n    - Matched Keywords: [List]\\n    - Unmatched Keywords: [List]\\n  - Projects Match:\\n    - Score: [Value - Float]\\n    - Matched Keywords: [List]\\n    - Unmatched Keywords: [List]\\n  - Overall Summary: [String summarizing the candidate's strengths and weaknesses based on the resume-job match. Highlights key areas of alignment and gaps.]\\n\\nResume Match Recommendation: [String suggesting a course of action based on the match_score and detailed analysis]\\n\\nII. Interview Summary:\\n[Summary of the interview process, including the flow, candidate's communication style, and overall impression.]\\n\\nIII. Technical Assessment:\\n[Evaluated using task4 - AnswerEvaluator]\\n\\n  - Question 1: [Technical Question]\\n    - Answer: [Candidate's Answer]\\n    - Relevance: [Score - 0-5]\\n    - Depth: [Score - 0-5]\\n    - Confidence: [Score - 0-5]\\n    - Technical Accuracy: [Score - 0-5]\\n    - Overall Score: [Value - Float]\\n    - Feedback: [String]\\n\\n  - Question 2: [Technical Question]\\n    - Answer: [Candidate's Answer]\\n    - Relevance: [Score - 0-5]\\n    - Depth: [Score - 0-5]\\n    - Confidence: [Score - 0-5]\\n    - Technical Accuracy: [Score - 0-5]\\n    - Overall Score: [Value - Float]\\n    - Feedback: [String]\\n\\n  [Add more technical questions and answers as needed]\\n\\nAverage Technical Assessment Score: [Value - Float]\\n\\nIV. Be